instruct_text: Welcome to the job simulator task!
In this experiment you will listen to 12 short stories.
During some of these stories, we will ask you to take on the perspective of a type of job.
In other words, you should try to listen to the story from the perspective of that job. This is called “job simulation.”
You will be told the job to simulate before each story.
Some stories, however, will not have any job assigned to them, and you can simply listen to the story.
In this part of the experiment outside of the scanner, we will introduce you to four perspectives you will be asked to take on.
For each perspective, you'll also learn 4 questions associated with it to use when listening to a story.
We encourage you to keep these questions in mind while listening to the story and simulating the associated perspective.
When you are in the scanner, you will listen to the 12 short stories.
Before listening to each story, you may be assigned one of the perspectives to take on while listening to it.
If a perspective is assigned, you’ll be quizzed on the 4 questions associated with it before listening.
You must pass this quiz to move on to the story.
There will be additional tasks after the story listening, but we will explain them when we come to them.
Are you reading to begin the training on the perspectives?
The four perspectives are as follows:

Q1: For how long has the initiator of the breakup been thinking about breaking up with his/her partner?
Q2: What is the initial reason stated by the initiator for why he/she is breaking up?
Q3: Does the person who is being broken up with want to break up, and what’s the reason stated by them for this?
Q4: Who wants what items back as a result of the breakup?
D1: What is the initial reason stated by the initiator for why he/she wanted to meet?
D2: Who wants how many letters burned as a result of the breakup?

Q4: How do the clients like the food?
D2: How do the clients like the chairs?

Q1: For how long has the couple been dating?
Q2: How many diamonds are on the ring, and what is the diamond color?
Q3: In/on what item is the ring presented?
Q4: Who does the new fiancee text first?
D1: For how long has the couple known the other was going to propose?
D2: Who does the new fiancee hug first?

Q1: What is the grocery store like upon entering?
Q2: What items do the clients pick out to buy?
Q3: How many checkout lanes are open, and which one do the clients step into?
Q4: How much are the groceries, and what method of payment do the clients use?
D1: What is the grocery store like when the clients leave?
D2: How many checkout lanes are closed, and which one do the clients step into?

instruct_text: You’ll become acquainted with them more in learning the 4 questions associated with each perspective.
For each perspective, you'll go through all four questions in a sequence.
Then you'll be presented with a quiz and have to indicate which questions you saw in the order in which they appeared in the sequence.
You'll indicate the question you select by pressing the number key corresponding to the number in front of the question.
If you make the wrong selection, you'll get the 4 questions presented in the correct order again and restart the quiz.
After you've passed the quizzes for each perspective, you'll do all of them a final time, but without seeing the correct order of the questions beforehand.
Press space to begin!
